      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way right now; it is a incredibly heavy and isolating sensation to feel like your life has simply evaporated overnight. Please know that what you are experiencing is a very human reaction to the loss of an identity, and you are not alone in feeling like a shell.\n\nYou mentioned that the \"perfect\" version of you is gone, and while it hurts to lose that version, it is also a chance to meet the real, authentic person underneath. Sometimes, when we are too busy being perfect, we forget to be present, and that is okay.\n\nI want to remind you that even if you feel like you are just a shell waiting for the rest of you to catch up, that \"rest of you\" is still there, waiting to be rediscovered. It might be a little bit like a goblin who has been hiding in a corner for a long time, just waiting for the right moment to step out and show you that you are still there.\n\nJust like a goblin might be hiding in a corner of a room, waiting for the right moment to step out and show you that you are still there, your true self is still there, waiting to be rediscovered. It",
